The extinction coefficient (k) is directly proportional to absorption coefficient $(\alpha),k$ can be obtained from the relation  as;
$$k= \frac{\alpha \lambda}{4 \pi}$$
where $\lambda$ is the wavelength of light.
The variation of the refractive index 'n' can be calculated by;
$$n= \frac{1+ \sqrt{R}}{1- \sqrt{R}}$$
where R is reflectance. Refractive index 'n' determines how reflective and refractive a film made from this material will be .
